            <title>[JCR-2594] Make cache limits configurable</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/JCR-2594</link>
                <project id="10591" key="JCR">Jackrabbit Content Repository</project>
                        <description>The cache settings of the CacheManager class (&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/JCR-619&quot; title=&quot;CacheManager (Memory Management in Jackrabbit)&quot;&gt;&lt;strike&gt;JCR-619&lt;/strike&gt;&lt;/a&gt;) can be adjusted programmatically (&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/JCR-725&quot; title=&quot;Configuration of CacheManager memory sizes&quot;&gt;&lt;strike&gt;JCR-725&lt;/strike&gt;&lt;/a&gt;), but it would be nice if there was also a way to set them with system properties or ideally as a part of the repository configuration.</description>
