                    <comment id="12854871" author="jukkaz" created="Thu, 8 Apr 2010 10:06:45 +0100"  >In revision 931838 I added support for the following system properties:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;org.apache.jackrabbit.maxCacheMemory - max memory used for all caches (in bytes, default 16MB)&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;org.apache.jackrabbit.maxMemoryPerCache - max memory used for a single cache (in bytes, default 4MB)&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;org.apache.jackrabbit.minMemoryPerCache - min memory used for a single cache (in bytes, default 128kB)&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;org.apache.jackrabbit.cacheResizeInterval - cache resize interval (in ms, default 1s)&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
Merged to the 2.1 branch in revision 931840.</comment>
